This whitepaper introduces a new Decentralized Streaming Network (DSN) and Theta, a newÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
blockchain and token as the incentive mechanism for the DSN.Â Â 
Â 
DSN and the Theta protocol solve various challenges the video streaming industry faces today.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
First, Theta tokens are used as an incentive to encourage individual users to share theirÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
redundant memory and bandwidth resources as caching nodes for video streams. ThisÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
improves the quality of stream delivery and solves the â€œlast-mileâ€ delivery problem, the mainÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
bottleneck for traditional stream delivery pipelines, especially for high resolution high bitrateÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
360Â° virtual reality (VR) streams. Second, with sufficient amount of caching nodes, the majorityÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
of viewers will pull streams from peering caching nodes. This significantly reduces contentÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
delivery network (CDN) bandwidth costs, which is a major concern for video streaming sites.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
Lastly, the Theta network greatly improves the streaming market efficiency by streamlining theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
video delivery process. For example, advertisers can target end viewers at a lower cost andÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
reward influencers more transparently.Â 
Â 
Â 
The Theta blockchain introduces three novel concepts:Â 
Â 

Reputation Dependent Mining: â€‹In the Theta protocol, the caching nodes play the roleÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
of miners in the blockchain. The block reward is not a constant, but depends on theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
reputation score of the caching node that mined the block. To obtain more miningÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
rewards, miners not only spend computation power to mine blocks, but also relayÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
video streams to downstream viewers to increase their reputation scores.Â 
Â 
Global Reputation Consensus: â€‹We propose a mechanism for the Theta network toÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
reach the global consensus on the reputation scores for each caching node.Â 
Â 
Proof-of-Engagement: We introduce a novel Proof-of-Engagement scheme to proveÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
that viewers legitimately consume the video streams, providing better transparency toÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
advertisers and a basis for viewers to earn Theta tokens for engaging with the contentÂ 
Â 

Â 
This white paper will describe these concepts and the Theta blockchain in detail. Phase I of theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
Theta network will launch with the issuance of ERC20-compliant tokens during the token sale.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
