Bootstrapping The NetworkÂ 

Â 
The above discussion assumes a fully decentralized architecture where all the ingest andÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
caching nodes come from users. To realize this long term vision, we need a sufficient numberÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
of users to participate, which may take some time. To â€‹bootstrap â€‹the network, we propose aÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
hybrid architecture that works with the existing CDN networks and the decentralized cachingÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
nodes.Â 

Â  Â 
Â 

                    Traditional CDN               Hybrid ArchitectureÂ 
Â 

Figure 4. â€‹Left - Traditional CDNâ€‹, where all the viewers connect directly to the POP servers. For nodes geographically far awayÂ 
from the POP servers, the stream quality may be lower (the dashed connections). â€‹Right - Hybrid Architecture â€‹where viewerÂ 
nodes can pull stream from caching nodes that are geographically closer than the POP servers, resulting in better streamingÂ 
quality.Â 

Â 
Â 
Figure 4 illustrates the hybrid architecture and compares it with traditional CDN networks.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
Whereas in the traditional CDN, every node pulls the stream directly from POP servers, in theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
hybrid architecture, only a subset of nodes pull the stream from POP servers. Other nodesÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
simply pull the stream from their peer caching nodes which provide better and more effectiveÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
connection. The caching nodes thus augment the traditional CDN backbones with more cachingÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
layers for end viewers geographically far away from the POPs. We note that this hybridÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
architecture applies to both video on demand and live streaming scenarios since traditionalÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
CDN networks work similarly.Â 
Â 
The advantage of bootstrapping with the hybrid architecture is important. â€‹The DSN is fullyÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
functional even with only a single caching nodeâ€‹. Furthermore, as will be discussed later, theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
caching node can mine new Theta tokens while providing the caching and video relayingÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
services. â€‹This provides strong economic incentives for more users to join the cachingÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
network over timeâ€‹. As more user contributed nodes join the DSN, the stream deliveryÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
capability of the network improves. At the point when there are sufficient amount of userÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
contributed nodes, the network can run on its own without the traditional CDN backbone.Â 

12Â 



How Theta Tokens Work in the DSNÂ 
Â 
Theta tokens work as a long-term sustainable incentive mechanism to motivate variousÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
stakeholders to participate in the DSN. It is tempting to design the incentive mechanism basedÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
on the traditional peer-to-peer model where the end viewers send Theta tokens to cachingÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
nodes in exchange for the stream relay service. However, such a scheme is impractical sinceÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
ad-supported viewers today on Twitch or YouTube, for example, are used to free videoÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
streams. â€‹We need an incentive mechanism to motivate the caching nodes to relay the videoÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
stream in absence of Theta tokens collected from viewers. For this purpose, we propose toÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
have the caching nodes play the roles of Theta miners. Similar to miners in other blockchains,Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
they validate Theta token transactions and assemble new blocks to obtain mining rewards.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
However, as detailed later in the whitepaper, we design the mechanism such that for a cachingÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
node, â€‹the more video stream relaying work it conducts, the higher mining rewards it getsâ€‹.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
This motivates the caching nodes to relay video streams in addition to mining new blocks.Â 
Â 
In this section, we will start by listing the stakeholders in the streaming ecosystem. We thenÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
describe how the Theta tokens flow among them and tie them together. Finally, we discussÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
how Theta improves the efficiency of the streaming market in the DSN.Â 

Â 

Video Streaming StakeholdersÂ 
Â 
The decentralized video streaming ecosystem has the following key stakeholders:Â 
Â 

â— Caching Nodes: They provide caching services to improve the video stream delivery.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
They are rewarded for the caching service they provide to the end viewers.Â 

Â 
â— Viewers: They are the end consumers of the video content. Viewer attention is theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

most important asset in the video streaming ecosystem. Viewers can be optionallyÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
rewarded for their attention and engagement with the video stream and withÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
advertisements .Â 11

Â 
â— Ingest Nodes: They provide the ingest service for the live streams, generating variousÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

stream resolutions, bitrates, etc. They are rewarded for providing this service to theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
caching nodes.Â 

Â 
â— Influencers/Streaming Sites: They are the producers of the video content. In the liveÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

streaming context, these influencers are also known as â€‹streamersâ€‹. In the video onÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
demand context, influencers are also referred to as â€‹content creatorsâ€‹. They will beÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
rewarded with Theta tokens for producing the content.Â 

Â 
â— Advertisers: The goal of advertisers is to promote their products and services to endÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

viewers. To achieve this, advertisers will spend Theta tokens as part of theirÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
advertising budget to sponsor influencers and video streams through video adsÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
including pre-rolls, mid-rolls and other formats.Â 

