Â 
Here || is the string concatenation operator. â€‹pkâ€‹i and â€‹pkâ€‹j are the public key of caching node â€‹i andÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
viewer node â€‹jâ€‹, respectively. â€‹block_hashâ€‹k is the hash of block â€‹kâ€‹, the most recently confirmedÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
block in the current longest chain. The viewer node â€‹j â€‹needs to return the â€‹nonce* that attains theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â   Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
minimal hash value it found before the next block is added to the longest chain. Whenever aÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
new block is confirmed, the caching node sends a new puzzle to its downstream viewers,Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
where in the new puzzle, the â€‹block_hashâ€‹k parameter in Formula (3) to point to the newly addedÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
