the time required to mine each new block is relatively a constant, one can determine whetherÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
the corresponding block, and hence the service certificate were generated within the given timeÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
window.Â 
Â 
Once a caching node mines a new block, it propagates the block to other caching nodes in theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
network for validation. For a caching node to validate a new block, in addition to verifying theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
transactions and the PoW puzzle solution, it needs to verify that the reputation score isÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
computed correctly based on the service certificates. In the following section, we will discussÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
how the global consensus on the reputation score can be formed.Â 
