It can be shown that since each validator miner picks the â€‹k set of certificates at random, asÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
more caching miner nodes join the network, the probability that the proposer miner can give anÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
incorrect reputation score and yet get block confirmations from all honest validator minersÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
approaches zero. The formal analysis is omitted here.Â 
Â 
Furthermore, since each validator miner now only needs to validate a small subset ofÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
certificates, the amount of data the validator miners need to download is greatly reduced. If aÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
validator miner identified an invalid set, it just need to propagate that set of certificates throughÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
the networks, which should not add much overhead since each set only contains a smallÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
number of certificates.Â 

23Â 



Theta Token Issuance ModelÂ 
Â 
Phase I of the Theta network will issue a fixed number of ERC20-compliant application tokensÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
with utility and functionality on the SLIVER.tv and other video platforms including:Â 
Â 

â— Enabling end-user viewers to gift Theta tokens to influencers directly or purchaseÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
virtual items and goods which can then be gifted to influencers.Â 

Â 
â— Allowing advertisers and brand sponsors to fund their advertising campaigns withÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

Theta tokens. These Theta tokens will automatically be used to reward influencersÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
whose video streams these ads will be displayed in, and optionally, advertisers canÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
reward viewers for their attention to the stream content and advertisements.Â 
Â 

â— Providing end-users with the ability to purchase premium content, virtual goods andÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
other paid products and services.Â 

Â 
With the full launch of the native Theta network and tokens in phase II, â€‹miners will have a fixedÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
amount of Theta tokens they can mine each year , similar to Ethereum, for two primaryÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 17

reasons:Â 
Â 

â— First, this ensures that there is always an incentive for the caching nodes to relay theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
video streams to improve their reputation and thus mining rewards. If the total ThetaÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
token supply has an upper limit, the caching nodes will not be motivated to relay theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
video streams after all the Theta tokens are mined.Â 

Â 
â— Second, it is expected that a portion of the Theta tokens will be lost each year due toÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

transmission to addresses that are no longer accessible. Moreover, Theta tokensÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
might be lost due to loss of private keys, or token destruction by purposely sending toÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
an address that never had an associated private key generated. It is expected thatÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
eventually the expected rate of annual loss will balance the rate of issuance.Â Â 

Â 

Anti-fraud ConsiderationsÂ 
Â 

â— Fake Service Certificatesâ€‹: As discussed earlier, if a malicious miner try to forge serviceÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
certificates, its expected mining reward actually decreases. Thus, a rational minerÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
would not try to forge service certificates. We will provide a more detailed analysis inÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
the Appendix.Â 

Â 
â— Service Certificate Withholding Attackâ€‹: A malicious viewer might withhold the bestÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

nonce it finds. However, we note that the difficulty level of finding a nonce thatÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
reflects the service time is reasonable for a typical PC, unlike the extremely difficultÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
Bitcoin mining puzzle as of today. Hence, it is relatively easy to detect such attacksÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
statistically. If a viewer is identified to withhold the best nounce it finds, the upstreamÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
caching node can simply terminates the video relay service.Â Â 

Â 

17 https://blog.ethereum.org/2014/04/10/the-issuance-model-in-ethereum/Â 

24Â 



â— Stream Relay Denial Attackâ€‹: A malicious caching node might deny service requestÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
from viewers and just mine for the tokens. We show here that this would actuallyÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
reduce its mining reward. As discussed earlier, the reputation score of a caching nodeÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
depends on the amount of video streams to the end viewers in a â€‹recent time windowâ€‹.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
Therefore, if a caching node is inactive for a certain amount of time, its reputationÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
would decrease, which in turn, would reduce the mining rewards it can obtain. ToÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
maximize mining reward in the end, the dominant strategy for a caching node is toÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
serve viewers consistently.Â 

Â 

Smart Streaming ContractsÂ 
Â 
The Theta blockchain supports a set of specialized smart contracts which are novel and can beÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
utilized to implement several scenarios which will help facilitate reward collection andÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
distribution between various players in a distributed streaming and entertainment ecosystem.Â Â 

Incentive ContractÂ 
Â 
The Theta blockchain supports a specialized smart contract called â€‹incentive contractâ€‹. AnÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
incentive contract is designed for several use cases which may involve a large number ofÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
different parties. Rather than require complex application logic, this smart-contract simplifiesÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
the process of collecting and distributing tokens based on certain pre-defined criteria andÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
allocations across different parties, some of whom may not be identified until later.Â 
Â 
We believe the Incentive contract is a novel concept which will have many uses, including butÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
not limited to:Â 
Â 

â— Advertisers rewarding viewers and streamersâ€‹. In this case, the incentive contractÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
serves as a way to deposit tokens in a decentralized advertising network, which areÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
drawn upon by various parties as the advertisements are shown and watched. TheÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
tokens get spread across multiple parties, including one or more streamers, and anyÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
number of viewers (ranging from a few thousand to as high as a few million), basedÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
upon proof of engagement. The streamers may be identified at the start, or they mayÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
be added later. The allocation may be specified based on percentages (for example,Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
50% to streamers and 50% to viewers) or other ways, and the contract is depleted overÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
time based on viewership, etc.Â Â 

Â 
â— Viewers can gift rewards to multiple parts of the streaming chainâ€‹. An incentiveÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

contract filled by a viewer for a specific streamer can also benefit the ingest nodes andÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
caching nodes that brought the stream to a specific viewer.Â 

Â 
â— Gift contract for multiple streamersâ€‹. A viewer may want to gift tokens as they areÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

earned to multiple streamers. An incentive contract can be used to set up these gifts,Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
which can be allocated across multiple parties.Â Â 

Â 
â— Paid/Premium video contentâ€‹. The concept of an incentive contract can be used toÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

support paid/premium content in the network in the future. See â€œFuture Workâ€ section.Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
To watch paid content, a viewer must put tokens into an incentive contract, which getsÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

25Â 



split based upon pre-defined allocations with the content owner (who may or may notÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
be streaming it).Â 

Â 
â— Subscriptions and Decentralized Entertainment Networks (DEN)â€‹. Incentive contractsÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

can enabled premium services like a Netflix, Amazon Prime or Hulu to be built on topÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
of our decentralized video streaming network. Viewers can subscribe by allocatingÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
tokens into incentive contracts which get parsed out between the many contentÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
owners in the network and the streaming/bandwidth providers who enable theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
network.Â 

Â Â 
â— A miner can share mining rewards with viewers and with content streamersâ€‹. A minerÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 

can put a percentage of their rewards, their mined tokens, into an incentive contractÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
and these can be distributed to the streamers who own the content they areÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
streaming or share mining rewards with viewers.Â Â 

Â 
These smart contracts are executed by the caching miner nodes. Typically, in order for aÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
recipient to receive the payment, it needs to send a certain proof to the smart contract. UponÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
proof validation, the smart contract initiates the token reward, and the original funders of theÂ  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â  Â 
incentive contract do not need to be involved.Â 
